Apple has released iOS 12.1 to users, including South Africans, which brings an array of new features. This includes Group FaceTime, over 70 new emoji, and support for dual SIM with eSIM for the iPhone XS, XS Max, and XR. “This update also includes bug fixes and improvements,” said Apple. The software update was 470.2MB when checked by MyBroadband on an iPhone X. Details of the update are listed below.